tr.td: Reverted to version as of 02:12, 4 June 2010 (no, I have explicit instructions from the state, and the construction is still wrong with your version)

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 19:05, 14 June 2010

tr.td: please Zscout370, leave the coulors of the flags

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 02:12, 4 June 2010
Thumbnail for version as of 06:57, 3 June 2010

tr.td: The Government emailed me back and said Pantone 2768 is used on the state flag officially.

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 06:52, 3 June 2010

tr.td: Received Sec. 44.09.020 via email today. Complete overhaul. The yellow is Spanish yellow pms 1235 according to the state, but the blue is kept the same.

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 04:58, 16 May 2010

tr.td: This is designed on a mockup displayed in photograph with Benny Benson, Gov. Egan and Charlotte Benson. http://vilda.alaska.edu/cdm4/item_viewer.php?CISOROOT=/cdmg11&CISOPTR=395&REC=9 The mockup has stars 1/15 the fly length. The left-most star is cente

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 00:16, 16 May 2010

tr.td: I updated the fly to match the 2/3 of most U.S. Flags. The color of the stars was set to gold - as specified in State Law. Also, I set the Dipper star diameter to 1/10 the fly. The North Star is 1/10 the fly. The top of the Dipper's "handle" is centered

img.alt: Thumbnail for version as of 08:31, 14 May 2010

tr.td: Sec. 44.09.020. State flag states that the blue in the Alaska flag is the same as the US flag, so in this case, Pantone 281 C. I am not certain about the yellow color because the "proper form" is not shown at http://www.legis.state.ak.us/basis/folioproxy.
